/*write a program to insert an element into an array to the nth position without using any inbuilt function */


1) Download Eclipse.
2) Create workspace.
3) Create Java Project "HeadspinPrograms".
4) Under src folder create class "InsertNthElement".
5) To insert nth element in the array, the pre requisite required is the number of elements in the array, position where the value needs to be inserted and the value.
6) Import the java.util.Scanner package.
7) Run the program.


Sample Output shared below:

Enter number of elements you want in Array:
5
Enter all the elements:
4
5
6
2
1
Enter the position where you want to insert element:
3
Enter the element you want to insert:
30
After Inserting
4,
5,
30,
6,
2,
1
